ding rather than mere civility, and provides incentive for continuing open-minded and shared inquiries into the important issues of life.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 26. Apr 2024) 0aTruth. 4aPhilosophy : American Philosophy. 4aPhilosophy : Epistemology. 4aPhilosophy : Ethics. 4aPhilosophy : Philosophy. 4aPolitics and Law : Political Philosophy. 7aPHILOSOPHY / Epistemology.2bisacsh08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertSUNY Press eBook Package 2018z978311149142440uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978143847135840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781438471358423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781438471358/original  a978-3-11-149142-4  SUNY Press eBook Package 2018b2018  aGBV-deGruyter-alles